body:
Feature request to support Webstorm IDE.

I discovered, that in Webstorm the flutter plugin is not found in plugins search. 
But the plugin can be installed manually by downloading https://plugins.jetbrains.com/plugin/9212
If manually installed in Webstorm the Create new project > Flutter is not visible.
Also flutter doctor dosn't check for Webstorm IDE.

comment_data.body: Also not found in PhpStorm's plugins search.
Also +1ing my request for WebStorm support.
hey webstorm 2018 cant install this package and again not found in plugins search.

We no long build the plugin for WebStorm - it didn't offer the best support once flutter added the ability to have native (android / iOS) plugins. I'd suggest trying IntelliJ Community Edition or Android Studio.
Now Flutter already supports web development, but also support WebStorm?
@weihongyu12 My personal effort on Flutter supports on WebStorm: https://plugins.jetbrains.com/plugin/14718

title: Support Webstorm IDE
